Colegio de Montalban - Centralized Campus Smart Map System (CDM-CCSMS) developed by Data Management Solutions (DMS).
Your privacy is of utmost importance to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard the information you provide to us through the use of our program.
1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information: When you use CDM-CCSMS, we collect the following personal information: Name Last Name Student Number Email Address
2. How We Use Your Information
2.1 Providing Services: We utilize the information collected to facilitate the functionality of CDM-CCSMS, offering personalized experiences, and addressing inquiries or requests.
2.2 Communication: Your email address may be used to communicate updates, announcements, and other pertinent information regarding CDM-CCSMS.
3. Information Sharing
We do not share your information with third parties except as outlined below:
We may share data with third-party service providers to assist in operating, maintaining, and improving CDM-CCSMS. These service providers are contractually obligated to uphold data protection standards and are restricted from using your information for any other purpose.
4. Data Security
4.1 Security Measures: We employ industry-standard security measures to safeguard your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.
4.2 Data Retention: Your information is retained for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes stated in this Privacy Policy, unless extended retention is mandated or permitted by law.
5. Your Choices
5.1 Opt-Out: You have the option to opt-out of receiving communications from us by following provided instructions in our communications or by directly contacting us.
5.2 Access and Update: You may access and update your personal information by contacting us directly.
6. Changes to this Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy may undergo revisions to reflect changes in operational practices, legal requirements, or regulatory standards. We will notify you of significant alterations by posting the updated version on our website or through other suitable channels.
7. Contact Us Should you have any queries or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please reach out to us at [contact email].
